-- MOVES-Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi UFJ names new EMEA chief
-- By Clare Hutchison
-- Mon Oct 06, 2014 05:05AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Oct 6 (Reuters) - The Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi UFJ (BTMU) [MTFGI.UL] <8306.T> said on Monday it had promoted Masato Miyachi to chief executive officer for Europe, the Middle East and Africa (EMEA), as it seeks to boost its presence in the region.

Masato joined the Bank of Tokyo, BTMU's predecessor, in 1984 and has held a number of roles within the firm. He was appointed deputy CEO for EMEA in 2013.